e
 e = \sum_{n \ge 0} \frac{1}{n!} \\ b! e = \sum_{n \ge 0} \frac{b!}{n!} = \sum_{0 \le n \le b} \frac{b!}{n!} + \sum_{n \ge b} \frac{b!}{n!} 
 S = \sum_{n > b} \frac{1}{(b + 1) (b + 2) \ldots n}   = \sum_{k \ge 1} \frac{1}{(b + 1)(b + 2) \ldots (b + k)}   < \sum_{k \ge 1} b^{-k} 
 \sum_{k \ge 1} b^{-k} = b^{-1} \sum_{k \ge 0} b^{-k} = b^{-1} \cdot \frac{1}{1 - b^{-1}} = \frac{1}{b - 1} \le 1 
